  "prompt": "What should be my individual subject scores in NEET 2017?",
  "response": "I'm unable to access personal data or individual exam scores, including NEET 2017 results. However, I can guide you on how to find and interpret your NEET scores:\n\n### **1. Check Your Official NEET Result:**\n- **Official Website:** Visit the official NEET website or the specific portal provided by the conducting authority for NEET 2017 results.\n- **Login Credentials:** Use your application number/password or other required credentials to log in.\n- **Download Scorecard:** Once logged in, you should be able to download your scorecard, which will detail your overall score as well as sectional (subject-wise) scores.\n\n### **2. Understanding NEET Scorecard:**\nNEET typically scores candidates based on three subjects:\n- **Physics**\n- **Chemistry**\n- **Biology (Botany & Zoology combined)**\n\nEach correct answer usually awards **4 marks**, and each incorrect answer deducts **1 mark**. There is **no negative marking** for questions left unanswered.\n\n### **3. Calculating Individual Subject Scores:**\nIf you've attempted to keep track of your answers, you can estimate your subject-wise scores using the formula:\n\n\\[\n\\text{Subject Score} = (4 \\times \\text{Number of Correct Answers}) - (\\text{Number of Incorrect Answers})\n\\]\n\n**Example:**\nIf in Physics you answered 35 questions correctly and 5 incorrectly:\n\\[\n\\text{Physics Score} = (4 \\times 35) - 5 = 140 - 5 = 135\n\\]\n\nRepeat this calculation for Chemistry and Biology to get your individual subject scores.\n\n### **4. Contacting NEET Authorities:**\nIf you're facing issues accessing your score or if there's a discrepancy, it's best to contact the official NEET support or the conducting body for assistance.\n\n### **5. Future Reference:**\nFor future exams:\n- **Keep Track:** Maintain a detailed record of your answers during practice tests.\n- **Use Official Resources:** Always refer to official NEET resources for the most accurate information.\n- **Stay Updated:** Ensure you're aware of the latest NEET guidelines and scoring patterns, as they can change over the years.\n\nIf you have any specific questions about interpreting your scores or need guidance on preparation strategies based on your performance, feel free to ask!",
